3- It is a SQLAlchemy core function used to: Establish a connection to a database , Create a database engine object,Configure how your app talks to the database (e.g., SQLite, MySQL, PostgreSQL)

3-ORM - An ORm has tools to convert ("map") between objects in code and database tables("relations")
Suppose you have pets table so you create a class Pet so this class is a responsible of the crud part of this table so we are basically mapping for this object class Pet to table class pets
